  "full_text_flowing_modernisation_text_block": "Internal Affairs\nHe who is the adorner of the throne of the Caliphate and the State, and the bestower of ornament upon the seat of majesty and sultanate,\nHis Excellency Ghazi Sultan Mahmud Khan II, having been in declining health for a few months,\nalthough—in accordance with the unchangeable decree of destiny—the treatments executed by skilled physicians\nand measures proved ineffective, the thread of his delicate, jewel-measuring life\nwas severed from the mortal coil; and on Monday, the nineteenth day of this month of Rabi' al-Thani,\nat dawn, he walked into the rose-garden palace of the Hereafter. And the worthy heir to the crown and throne,\nhis young and fortunate prince, the majestic, noble, awesome, and powerful Sultan Abdülmecid\nKhan, our Lord, by inheritance and right, his accession to the heaven-destined throne of the Caliphate\noccurred with imperial auspiciousness; whereupon all the great viziers, illustrious ulema,\nmilitary commanders, statesmen, and the truth-marked servants of the Sublime Sultanate gathered at the Imperial Palace,\nand in accordance with the ancient custom and excellent rites of the Exalted State, the ceremony of allegiance was executed,\nand prayers for the prolongation of the life, fortune, and majesty, and the abundance of glory, splendor, and sovereignty of His Imperial Majesty\nwere offered and performed with a tongue of sincerity. Following this, the late Sovereign,\nhe who nests in eternity, His Excellency's mercy-embroidered, heaven-bound funeral bier, after the performance of the prayer,\nwas carried with the necessary glorifications and required honors in an angel-approved procession,\nand was delivered and conveyed to the light-filled tomb prepared for him. As the Sovereign\nwhose station is Paradise, His Excellency, sleeps in the dormitory of the Creator's mercy, and his victory-filled soul\nbenefits from the lights of divine forgiveness, may the Lord of Truth and Absolute Bountiful One\ngrant that our benefactor to whom we owe everything, who now sits upon the world-guarding throne and occupies the high seat of the Ottoman dynasty,\nour majestic Lord, be accompanied by divine confirmations and lordly bounties,\nmaking him the commander of the sultanate and glory; and may the happy existence of His Imperial Majesty\nadorn the diadem of the Caliphate with perfect health, wellness, and increased pleasure and joy for as long as the sun and moon revolve,\nand commanding the mark of majesty and fortune; so that all those who pray for him, his servants, and all the inhabitants\nand residents of the kingdoms and cities may always acquire all kinds of\nexpansion and desires under the shadow of his sublime sultanate. And may his imperial time of felicitous conjunction, through the greatness of his glory\nand for the honor of the pure name of the glorious Prophet, be made a marketplace of justice and happiness; this obligatory prayer\nhas been repeated.\n\nOn the morrow of the aforesaid day, Tuesday, the imperial personage marked by majesty,\nas it is incumbent upon the endeavor of ruling and the necessary charge of the majesty-equipped crowned Excellency,\nby the success granted by Him (Glory be to Him and Exalted is He), commenced and undertook the performance of the affairs of his sublime sultanate;\nand from the blessed, light-clear innate talent of His Imperial Majesty, actually and independently,\nthe sublime office of the Grand Vizierate and the Great Absolute Agency was conferred upon the most magnificent of ministers...",
  "summary": "This document from the Takvîm-i Vekâyi (July 11, 1839) formally announces the death of Sultan Mahmud II and the accession of his son, Sultan Abdülmecid I. It details that Mahmud II, after months of illness which physicians could not cure due to destiny's decree, passed away on Monday, 19 Rabi' al-Thani 1255. The text describes the immediate accession of Abdülmecid to the throne, the gathering of state officials (viziers, ulema, military) at the Imperial Palace for the traditional ceremony of allegiance (bi'at), and the subsequent funeral procession and burial of the late Sultan. The text concludes with elaborate prayers for the new Sultan's reign, health, and justice, and notes that on the following day (Tuesday), Sultan Abdülmecid immediately commenced his imperial duties, specifically mentioning the appointment of the Grand Vizier (Sadâret-i 'Uzmâ)."
